    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCannot do:\n\n```vim\nset pumborder=round\n```\n\nLike in Vim.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:set pumborder=round\n```\n> E474: Invalid argument: pumborder=round\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNot really a bug but wanted to highlight the difference between Neovim and Vim. I think historically Neovim introduced these options first with `'winborder'` so its `'rounded'` option took precedence when it came to implementing `'pumborder'`.\n\nShould Neovim accept `'round'` and interpret it as `'rounded'`?\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0-dev commit f58d24040a32e5f28f57048657c40e302894b314\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1887\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTerminal.app\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nMacPorts",
