            "body": "It differs in a few more ways:\n\n- `ascii` option\n- `margin` is roughly equivalent to Neovim's `solid`\n- Vim's custom is prefixed `custom:` before the characters and uses `;` as a delimiter\n- the option itself can have additional flags, e.g. `double,margin,shadow`\n\nvim: [`:h 'pumborder'`](https://vimhelp.org/options.txt.html#%27pumborder%27)",
